        {tc.fragility.limitationNote}
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 5b. Sector Internal Fragility ────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-1">{tc.sectorFrag?.heading ?? 'Sector Internal Fragility'}</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">{tc.sectorFrag?.subheading ?? 'How far apart are the cheap and expensive halves within each sector — current snapshot.'}</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6">{tc.sectorFrag?.note ?? 'Sectors with ≥ 4 companies. n ≥ 8: quartile split; n < 8: median split. Sorted by spread descending.'}</p>

      <div class="space-y-3">
        {sectorFragRows.map(row => (
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-1">
              <span class="text-xs font-medium text-gray-700">{row.sector}</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-400">n={row.n}</span>
            </div>
            <!-- Range bar: full bar = Narrative, inset = Core -->
            <div class="relative h-6 bg-gray-100 rounded-sm overflow-hidden">
              <!-- Narrative bar (orange, background) -->
              <div
                class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 bg-orange-400/50 rounded-sm"
                style={`width:${maxSectorNarr > 0 ? (row.narrativeMedian / maxSectorNarr * 100).toFixed(1) : 0}%`}
              />
              <!-- Core bar (teal, foreground overlay) -->
              <div
                class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 bg-teal-400/70 rounded-sm"
                style={`width:${maxSectorNarr > 0 ? (row.coreMedian / maxSectorNarr * 100).toFixed(1) : 0}%`}
              />
            </div>
            <!-- Values -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mt-1 text-[11px]">
              <span class="text-teal-700 font-mono">Core {row.coreMedian.toFixed(2)}</span>
              <span class="text-gray-300">·</span>
              <span class="text-orange-700 font-mono">Narrative {row.narrativeMedian.toFixed(2)}</span>
              <span class="text-gray-300">·</span>
              <span class={`font-mono font-semibold ${row.spread === maxSectorSpread ? 'text-orange-700' : 'text-gray-600'}`}>
                Spread {row.spread.toFixed(2)}{row.spread === maxSectorSpread ? ' ↑' : ''}
              </span>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="mt-6 border-l-2 border-gray-200 pl-4 space-y-2.5">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-0.5">Automotive — the most internally split sector</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            Traditional automakers (low RG, earnings-anchored) sit in the same sector as high-narrative EV
            companies. The within-sector spread of {sectorFragRows.find(r => r.sector === 'Automotive')?.spread.toFixed(2) ?? '—'}
            is the widest in the panel, making Automotive more internally divergent than even Technology.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-0.5">Semiconductors: growth premium concentrated in the top half</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            The sector spans from mature foundry-model companies (TSMC-type, lower RG) to pure-play AI
            infrastructure names trading at high multiples of smoothed earnings. Spread of
            {sectorFragRows.find(r => r.sector === 'Semiconductors')?.spread.toFixed(2) ?? '—'}.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-0.5">Technology: smaller spread than expected</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            With the broadest company count, Technology shows a moderate spread of
            {sectorFragRows.find(r => r.sector === 'Technology')?.spread.toFixed(2) ?? '—'} —
            suggesting the label "Technology" covers a more homogeneous RG band than Automotive or Semiconductors.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 5c. Convergence to RG = 1 ────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-1">Convergence to Fair Value (RG = 1)</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">
        RG = 1 is the instrument's theoretical anchor: market cap equals ten times smoothed earnings.
        Do companies actually move toward it over time — or drift further away?
      </p>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6">
        Panel of {tN} companies with valid RG10 in both Q4 2023 and Q4 2025.
        Converging = distance to RG 1.0 decreased by &gt; 0.05; Diverging = increased by &gt; 0.05.
      </p>

      <!-- Summary bar -->
      <div class="flex gap-3 mb-6 flex-wrap">
        <div class="border border-teal-200 bg-teal-50/50 rounded-md px-5 py-3 min-w-[140px]">
          <p class="text-xs text-teal-600 font-medium uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Converging</p>
          <p class="text-3xl font-light text-teal-800" style="font-family:Georgia,serif">{convCount}</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-teal-500 mt-0.5">{convPct}% of panel</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-orange-200 bg-orange-50/50 rounded-md px-5 py-3 min-w-[140px]">
          <p class="text-xs text-orange-600 font-medium uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Diverging</p>
          <p class="text-3xl font-light text-orange-800" style="font-family:Georgia,serif">{divCount}</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-orange-500 mt-0.5">{100 - convPct}% of panel</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50/50 rounded-md px-5 py-3 min-w-[200px] flex-1">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 font-medium uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">By starting group</p>
          <div class="flex gap-4 mt-1 text-xs">
            <span><span class="text-teal-700 font-semibold">{coreConvPct}%</span> <span class="text-gray-500">of Core (RG &lt; 0.8) converging</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-4 mt-0.5 text-xs">
            <span><span class="text-orange-700 font-semibold">{narrConvPct}%</span> <span class="text-gray-500">of Narrative (RG &gt; 1.5) converging</span></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Top movers -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6">
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-teal-700 mb-2">Strongest convergence — approaching RG 1.0</p>
          <div class="space-y-1.5">
            {topConvergers.map(c => (
              <div class="border border-teal-100 bg-teal-50/40 rounded px-3 py-2 text-xs">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline">
                  <span class="font-medium text-gray-700">{c.company}</span>
                  <span class="font-mono text-teal-700">{c.rg23.toFixed(2)} → {c.rg25.toFixed(2)}</span>
                </div>
                <div class="text-gray-400 mt-0.5">
                  Distance to RG 1.0: {c.dist23.toFixed(2)} → {c.dist25.toFixed(2)}
                  <span class="text-teal-600 ml-1">({c.distDelta.toFixed(2)})</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-orange-700 mb-2">Strongest divergence — moving away from RG 1.0</p>
          <div class="space-y-1.5">
            {topDivergers.map(c => (
              <div class="border border-orange-100 bg-orange-50/40 rounded px-3 py-2 text-xs">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline">
                  <span class="font-medium text-gray-700">{c.company}</span>
                  <span class="font-mono text-orange-700">{c.rg23.toFixed(2)} → {c.rg25.toFixed(2)}</span>
                </div>
                <div class="text-gray-400 mt-0.5">
                  Distance to RG 1.0: {c.dist23.toFixed(2)} → {c.dist25.toFixed(2)}
                  <span class="text-orange-600 ml-1">(+{c.distDelta.toFixed(2)})</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Sector breakdown -->
      {convSectorRows.length > 0 && (
        <div class="mb-6">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3">Convergence rate by sector (n ≥ 3)</h3>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            {convSectorRows.map(row => (
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="text-xs text-gray-600 w-40 shrink-0">{row.sector}</span>
                <div class="flex-1 bg-gray-100 rounded-sm h-4 relative">
                  <div class="h-4 rounded-sm bg-teal-400/70"
                    style={`width:${row.convPct}%`} />
                </div>
                <span class="text-xs font-mono text-gray-700 w-10 shrink-0">{row.convPct}%</span>
                <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 shrink-0">n={row.n}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      )}

      <!-- Interpretation -->
      <div class="space-y-2.5">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-gray-300 pl-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-0.5">Core companies converge faster than Narrative</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            {coreConvPct}% of companies starting below RG 0.8 moved closer to fair value — likely via rising
            smoothed earnings, not falling prices. Only {narrConvPct}% of companies starting above RG 1.5
            corrected toward 1.0. The expensive tail is stickier than the cheap tail, which is consistent
            with the fragility hypothesis: narrative valuations resist downward revision.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-gray-300 pl-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-0.5">A soft internal validation</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            The majority of the panel ({convPct}%) moves in the direction RG theory predicts — toward
            the fair-value anchor. This does not prove predictive power, but it is consistent with the
            instrument's internal logic. The {100 - convPct}% diverging group — led by names like Tesla
            and Broadcom — represents the genuinely open question: will those correct, or has the
            smoothed-earnings baseline itself shifted?
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-gray-300 pl-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-0.5">Caveat: 2025 market cap bias</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            As with all 2025 observations: current market cap is used rather than end-of-quarter prices.
            Companies that report higher smoothed earnings in 2025 will mechanically show lower RG,
            appearing to converge even without a price correction.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 6. RG vs Simpler Metrics ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-1">{tc.metricComparison.heading}</h2>
